        "id": 5230
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-02-09T19:18:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Well, in the flushState version we will have had to have made all the intermediate flushing decisions ahead of time, so I think we will need it. That said the compatibility enforcement allows the final SkSurface to have greater limits - it just can have less resources.\n\nWe could just not enforce compatibility at all on the dest SkSurface (just blow past the budget) but I think we would still want these here to be able to add intermediate flushes.",
      "parentUuid": "1e8c8862_5c7f0d48",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 442,
        "startChar": 6,
        "endLine": 445,
        "endChar": 87
      },
      "revId": "1a90e58fa2525c496034cad1d6fc40e1777a7b8e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
