        "id": 5230
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-02-09T19:22:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ha - I fell behind on the comments. In the opList world we are not splitting the opLists based on these limits. For the opList implementation I intend to add partial flushing of opLists at flush time.\n\nIn the flushState world I think we will need to actually run the allocation algorithm to insert the intermediate flushes.",
      "parentUuid": "d0349f17_8a21edba",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 442,
        "startChar": 6,
        "endLine": 445,
        "endChar": 87
      },
